First, to check if a file is open, use `if(inputFile.is_open()){}`. `if(inputFile){}` will (I believe) perform something like `if(&amp;inputFile != 0x00000000){}`, which I don&#39;t think you want.
&lt;br&gt;If you are having trouble reading the file, use
```cpp
for(unsigned char i = 0; i &lt; ARRAY_SIZE; i++){
	inputFile &gt;&gt; numbers[i];					// note the `&gt;&gt;` operator
}
```
For `getLowest()`, I&#39;m  guessing you want something more like
```cpp
#define ARRAY_SIZE 12							// a macro
int getLowest(int* arrayNum, int&amp; smallest){
	int temp = 0;
	for(int i = 0; i &lt; ARRAY_SIZE; i++){		// in your code, if smallest was &gt; 
		if(temp &lt; arrayNum[i]){					// array length, run-time err
			temp = arrayNum[i];
		}
	}
	smallest = temp;
	return temp;
}
```
You just had a few critical errors in your code. I hope this helps.

